---
// src/pages/privacy-policy.astro
import SecondaryHero from "@/components/StaticSections/SecondaryHero.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Marketing from "../layouts/Marketing.astro";
import { SiteData, ContactData } from "@/content/SiteData";

const effectiveDate = "May 14, 2025";
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description={`How ${SiteData.title} collects and uses your information.`}>
  <SecondaryHero title={"Privacy Policy"}/>
  <section class="prose mx-auto my-8 px-[var(--spacing-lg)]">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Effective date:</em> {effectiveDate}</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information when you interact with {SiteData.title}:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact Details:</strong> Your name, email address, and phone number when you submit a form via Formspree.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device model, and other diagnostics collected via cookies and similar technologies.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages you visit, time spent on pages, clicks, and other interaction data to help us improve our site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to your inquiries and provide quotes or support.</li>
      <li>To monitor, maintain, and improve our website’s performance and security.</li>
      <li>To send you service updates or marketing messages if you opt in.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Forms and Data Submission</h2>
    <p>
      All form submissions are processed by <a href="https://formspree.io">Formspree</a>.  
      We do not store any form data on our own servers; Formspree securely forwards submissions to our inbox.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>
      We use cookies and similar tools to recognize you, remember preferences, and analyze site usage.  
      Any analytics, A/B testing, or advertising scripts you add in our <code>Marketing.astro</code> layout are automatically covered by this policy.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third‑Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      We rely on the following external providers:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Form Handling:</strong> Formspree for secure form processing.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics & Marketing:</strong> Any scripts configured in <code>Marketing.astro</code> (e.g., Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      {SiteData.title} does not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 16.  
      If you believe we have inadvertently done so, please contact us to request removal.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete your personal data.  
      To exercise any of these rights, please email us at <a href={`mailto:${ContactData.email}`}>{ContactData.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time.  
      Any changes will be posted here with a new “Effective date.”
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach us via:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${ContactData.email}`}>{ContactData.email}</a></li>
      <li>Phone:
        <ul>
          {ContactData.phone.map(({ type, number }) => (
            <li key={type}>
              <strong>{type.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + type.slice(1)}:</strong>
              <a href={`tel:${number}`}> {number}</a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Address: {ContactData.address}</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Dynamically include any marketing or analytics scripts -->
  <Marketing client:load />
</BaseLayout>
